article.headline: Illinois St. 86, Sacramento St. 69
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Anthony Slack scored 21 points and pulled down 10 rebounds Wednesday as Illinois State beat Sacramento State 86-69. Slack, who made 9 of 10 shots from the field, was one of five Illinois State (4-2) players in double digits. Boo Richardson scored 12 points, while Greg Dilligard and Roberto Fortes each had 11. Brandon Holtz chipped in 10 for the Redbirds, who led 39-28 at halftime. Sacramento State (4-4) shot just 44 percent while Illinois State made 60 percent of their field goals. The Redbirds also outrebounded Sacramento State 29-37. Angel Alamo led the Hornets with 16 points on 7-of-8 shooting. Alex Bausley had 13 points and Loren Leath added 12.
